revision.text:
{{short description|Categorisation of periods in Belizean history}} {{use dmy dates|date=June 2022}} {{use British English|date=June 2022}} [[File:Belize - Location Map (2013) - BLZ - UNOCHA.svg|thumb|upright=1.3|Belize {{small|/ 2013 map by UNOCHA}}]] The '''periodisation of Belizean history''' is the [[periodisation|division]] of [[History of Belize|Belizean]], [[History of the Maya civilization|Mayan]], and [[History of Mesoamerica|Mesoamerican history]] into named blocks of time, spanning the [[Settlement of the Americas|arrival of Palaeoindians]] to the present time. The [[pre-Columbian era]] is most often periodised by [[Mayanists]], who often employ four or five periods to discuss history prior to the [[Voyages of Christopher Columbus|arrival of Spaniards]]. The Columbian era is most often periodised by historians, and less often by Mayanists, who often employ at least four periods to discuss history up to the present time.
== Columbian == === Periods === The Columbian era of Belizean history is most often divided into four periods, ie the Spanish, Precolonial, Colonial, and Sovereign, all preceded by a portion of the pre-Columbian Postclassic period extending past 1492. These are most often defined or characterised in terms of distinguishing events occurring ''between'' each period, ie events separating one period from another, and less often in terms of distinguishing events, trends, or milestones occurring ''within'' each period. Generally, there has been less attention paid to the periodisation of the Columbian era of Belizean history, as opposed to its pre-Columbian era, resulting in broad concordance between the upper and lower bounds employed for each period in scholarly literature.{{citation needed|date=July 2022}} ==== Postclassic ==== {{see below|{{section link||Pre-Columbian}} below}} ==== Spanish ==== The Spanish period is most often characterised as the time span ''prior to'' the beginning or end of the Tipu rebellion, {{start and end dates|1638|6|6|1643|12|31|df=y}}, or to the latest Tipu ''reducción'' in {{start and end dates|1708|1|1|1708|12|31|df=y}}.{{sfn|Graham|2011|p=49}}{{citation needed|date=July 2022}}
==== Precolonial ==== The Precolonial period is most often characterised as the time span running ''to'' the date on which the British settlement in the Bay of Honduras was granted a colonial charter, ie {{start date|1862|2|12|df=y}}, or the date on which these letters patent were proclaimed, ie {{start date|1862|5|12|df=y}}.{{sfn|Burdon|1935|pp=246, 248}}
==== Colonial ==== The Colonial period is most often characterised as the time span running ''to'' the passage of the Belize Act in UK Parliament, the Constitution Act in the Belizean Parliament, or the date on which said acts came into force, known as the day on which Belize gained sovereignty or independence from the UK, ie {{start date|1981|9|21|df=y}}.{{citation needed|date=July 2022}}
==== Sovereign ==== The Sovereign ie Independent period is most often characterised as the time span running ''to'' the present. ==== Table ==== {| class="sortable" style="text-align: left;" |+ Defined upper and lower bounds of Columbian periods of Belizean history as per 20th and 21st century literature.{{notetag|Gregorian dates provided, unless otherwise noted.}} |- ! No ! class=unsortable style="width:11.875%;"| Name ! class=unsortable style="width:11.875%;"| Sub ! class=unsortable style="width:11.875%;"| Span ! style="width:11.875%;"| Date ! style="width:11.875%;"| Date ! class=unsortable style="width:11.875%;"| Event ! class=unsortable style="width:11.875%;"| Notes |- | rowspan=3 style="vertical-align: top;"| 1 | rowspan=3 style="vertical-align: top;"| Postclassic | rowspan=3 style="vertical-align: top;"| {{unbulleted list|Early|Late}} | rowspan=3 style="vertical-align: top;"| ''from'' latest Mayan monumental inscription ''to'' earliest Spanish contact ''or'' completion of Spanish conquest | style="vertical-align: top;"| {{start date|910|1|13|df=y}} | style="vertical-align: top;"| {{end date|910|1|13|df=y}} | style="vertical-align: top;"| Dedication of Itzimte Stela 6 | rowspan=3 style="vertical-align: top;"| cf{{hairspace}}{{notetag|Itzimte event in {{harvnb|Ebert|Prufer|Macri|Winterhalder|2015|p=342|loc=tab. 1 item no. 29}}, Long Count date 10.4.1.0.0 converted to Gregorian date using GMT correlation with 584283 constant, as per the [http://research.famsi.org/date_mayaLC.php online FAMSI calculator]. Bacalar event in {{harvnb|Chamberlain|1948|p=234}} (dated 'sometime during 1544') and {{harvnb|Jones|1989|p=43}} (dated 'at the end of 1544').}} |- | style="vertical-align: top;"| {{start date|1492|10|21|df=y}} | style="vertical-align: top;"| {{start date|1492|10|21|df=y}} | style="vertical-align: top;"| Arrival of Columbus |- | style="vertical-align: top;"| {{start date|1544|1|1|df=y}} | style="vertical-align: top;"| {{start date|1544|12|31|df=y}} | style="verti